# Seven Segment Display Allocation

| Display    | Function             |
| ---------- | -------------------- |
| D0 Digit 0 | Output Ones          |
| D0 Digit 1 | Output Tens          |
| D0 Digit 2 | Output Hundreds      |
| D0 Digit 3 | Blank                |
| D1 Digit 0 | Program Counter (PC) |
| D1 Digit 1 | Blank                |
| D1 Digit 2 | Current Opcode       |
| D1 Digit 3 | Current Operand      |

## Display Format

```text
[Hundreds][Tens][Ones][ ]

[ PC ][ ][Opcode][Operand]
```

### Example

```text
Output = 125

PC      = 6

Opcode  = B

Operand = 0
```

Display:

```text
125_

6_B0
```

This allows real-time monitoring of:

* CPU Output
* Current Program Counter
* Current Instruction Opcode
* Current Instruction Operand

